      <item>
        <title>FieldModel</title>
        <description>&lt;h2 id=&quot;field-properties&quot;&gt;Field Properties&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;title&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;title&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The title of the field.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;slug&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;slug&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A slugified version of the title of the field.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;handle&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;handle&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A camelcase version of the title, useful for referencing the field in a template.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;instructions&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;instructions&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The instructions given above the field in the admin dashboard.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;type&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;type&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The type of field this is. Example: Dropdown, RichText.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;required&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;required&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A boolean to represent whether or not the field is required in the admin dashboard.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;options&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;options&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An object that contains the various options available to the specific type of field. See FieldTypes for more.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;datecreated&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;dateCreated&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A UNIX timestamp for when the field was created.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
